  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0ba8\u0b9f\u0bb5\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd\u00a0 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bcb\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0b95\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b9a\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The next course of action should be decided with sufficient consensus - insists the National Peace Council",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "The President's House was occupied by the People's Movement (Arakalaya) protesters last Saturday. Meanwhile, President Gotabaya Rajapaksa went abroad this morning. The Prime Minister's office and the Rupavahini Corporation were occupied by protesters. An attempt was also made to occupy the Parliament building. All these incidents highlight the ongoing crisis in Sri Lanka and the people's loss of faith in the existing political institutions.",
        "Unfortunately, the insolent behavior of our MPs in Parliament in recent times has eroded faith in democratic institutions.",
        "Despite the revolutionary nature of the events taking place, it was seen that the President, the government and the security forces exercised admirable patience. People should agree to respect the law and constitution of the country. We will not accept that the rights of the people to express opposition are suppressed by using force in an anti-democratic manner through emergency law and curfew. It is necessary to act responsibly to avoid anarchy.",
        "The National Peace Council is dissatisfied and concerned about the conflicting communications between the President, the Prime Minister and the Speaker regarding the resignation of the President and his replacement. Based on this and the weakening of the mandates given by the people in the elections three years ago to the President and the Government, the National Peace Council has been asked by political leaders, civil society organizations and religious leaders. As proposed, the All Party demands the immediate formation of an interim government.",
        "It is appropriate for the major political parties to decide on who can form part of the interim government based on sufficient consensus among themselves.",
        "As the problems facing the country are very serious, it is important to take decisions based on consensus at this moment. There is a need to devise a framework for corruption-free economic restructuring, political reform and decentralization based on diverse social values \u200b\u200band accountability in a manner that can gain the support of the people and set the stage for an honest and free election as soon as possible.",
        "If this is done, the international community will be able to believe that Sri Lanka has a plan for the future. This will lead to assistance to ensure that the country emerges from the current economic crisis and political strife. This is the immediate need."
      ],
